# brain/ IS versioned on purpose — git diff over brain/ is how Overseer knows what changed.
# Do not ignore it.

# Your raw corpus and inbox are private and can be huge; keep them out of git by default.
# (The brain is a re-derivable index over them — losing brain/ is recoverable by re-folding;
#  committing your whole life is not what you want.) Remove these lines if you want them tracked.
corpus/**
!corpus/
!corpus/README.md
!corpus/.gitkeep
!corpus/*/
!corpus/*/.gitkeep

# This is the PUBLIC template, so the synthetic "Sam Rivera" seed is whitelisted below — it ships the
# worked example end-to-end (raw corpus → shards → nodes → index/journal). Your own material stays
# ignored: drop real files into corpus/ and they are never committed. For a private brain of your own,
# keep this list as-is and just fold; nothing real leaks.
!corpus/self/profile.md
!corpus/work/thesis-brief.md
!corpus/network/whoswho.md
!corpus/network/mara.txt
!corpus/network/devon.txt

inbox/**
!inbox/
!inbox/README.md
!inbox/.gitkeep

# OS / tooling cruft.
.DS_Store
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Never commit a stray secret even if one slips into the working tree.
*.env
.env
*.pem
*.key
*_secret*
